## Third-party code

Some files come from other projects and keep their original licenses. The
MIT terms above do not cover them.

* `harness/vendor/bip340_reference.py` and the BIP test vectors under
  `harness/vendor/` are unmodified copies from https://github.com/bitcoin/bips,
  licensed under **BSD-2-Clause**. See `harness/vendor/PROVENANCE.md` for the
  upstream commit and download date.

* `kmp/nip41/src/commonMain/kotlin/com/appollo41/nip41/Bech32.kt` is a
  verbatim subset of ACINQ's `bitcoin-kmp` `Bech32.kt`
  (https://github.com/ACINQ/bitcoin-kmp), licensed under **Apache-2.0**. The
  only changes from upstream are the `package` declaration and the omission
  of three Bitcoin-specific methods that NIP-19 does not use
  (`hrp(BlockHash)`, `encodeWitnessAddress`, `decodeWitnessAddress`). All
  retained declarations are byte-identical to upstream. The file header
  records the synced upstream commit.
